Spring REST Thymeleaf Tutorial

  This tutorial demonstrates server-side HTML rendering from OfficeFloor REST service methods
  using Thymeleaf.  The key difference from a JSON endpoint is the use of
  {{{/apidocs/net/officefloor/spring/starter/rest/view/ViewResponse.html}ViewResponse}} in place
  of <<<ObjectResponse\<T\>>>> — <<<ViewResponse.send(viewName)>>> hands off rendering to Spring's
  <<<ViewResolver>>> (Thymeleaf in this case).

  The tutorial shows a single <<<GET /greeting>>> endpoint that renders a personalised HTML page.

  {{{https://github.com/officefloor/OfficeFloor/tree/master/tutorials/springboot/SpringRestThymeleafHttpServer}Tutorial Source}}



*Maven dependency

%{snippet|id=tutorial|file=${basedir}/pom.xml|ignoreDownloadError=false}



*Application class

%{snippet|id=tutorial|file=${basedir}/src/main/java/net/officefloor/tutorial/springrestthymeleaf/SpringRestThymeleafApplication.java|ignoreDownloadError=false}



*Service method

  The service method takes three parameters injected by OfficeFloor:

   * <<<@RequestParam String name>>> — the query parameter from the URL

   * <<<Model>>> — the Thymeleaf model; attributes added here are available in the template

   * <<<ViewResponse>>> — the OfficeFloor view trigger; calling <<<send(viewName)>>> resolves and
     renders the template named <<<greeting>>> (i.e. <<<templates/greeting.html>>>)

%{snippet|id=tutorial|file=${basedir}/src/main/java/net/officefloor/tutorial/springrestthymeleaf/GreetingViewService.java|ignoreDownloadError=false}

  The YAML file names the class — no other configuration is needed:

%{snippet|file=${basedir}/src/main/resources/officefloor/rest/greeting.GET.yml|ignoreDownloadError=false}



*Thymeleaf template

  The template lives in <<<src/main/resources/templates/greeting.html>>>.  Thymeleaf substitutes
  <<<th:text="\$\{name\}">>> with the value added to the model:

%{snippet|file=${basedir}/src/main/resources/templates/greeting.html|ignoreDownloadError=false}



